<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1981-05-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Murine coronaviruses: the histopathology of disease induced by intranasal inoculation</TITLE><BODY>Mice inoculated intranasally with murine coronaviruses (mouse hepatitus viruses) were killed daily for seven days. Lung and liver sections stained by the immunopcroxidasc technique indicated that with three of the four strains examined viral localisation and replication in the lung preceded that found in (he liver. Thus, infection by the respiratory route may be of importance in the Iransmission of these viruses.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>